# {{.Name}} - Aone Sandbox Template

This is an Aone sandbox template project for Go.

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, make sure you have:

- An Aone sandbox API key
- Go installed
- The `aone` CLI installed

## Building Locally

```bash
make build
```

## Building The Template

```bash
aone sandbox template create {{.Name}}
```

The command reads `aone.sandbox.toml`, builds the Dockerfile, and writes the
resolved `template_id` back to the config file.

## Using The Template

```bash
aone sandbox create
```

## Template Structure

- `main.go` - Example Go entrypoint
- `Dockerfile` - Sandbox image definition
- `aone.sandbox.toml` - Template project config
- `Makefile` - Local build and run helpers
